originalText.text: Charmingly restored and converted residential facility for low-income tenants. The building was once home to Gouveneurs Hospital (circa; 1898) and is designated as a National Historical Landmark. It is wonderfully facilitated by the Community Access organization. I should well know; I am a gratified tenant. The historical building boasts a beautiful courtyard fountain, dedicated to early funder and philanthropist; the late Brooke Astor. She being daughter in-law to the wealthy John Jacob Astor, who perished on the ill-fated maiden voyage of the Titanic in 1915. I have a fantastic overview of the fountain from my window. Great place and neighborhood to live.
